column4: I know. I just have this machine (the only machine for now) that has to do: internet, photoshop and music. The most critical of them is not running yet (that's photoshop).

I managed to fix the Photoshop problem. For future reference if someone asks: install cabextract then install winetricks and at the end sudo apt-get remove wine after uninstalling has finished (it won't remove Photoshop) then sudo apt-get install wine.
